n boofi() -> i32 {\r\n        a\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nerror[E0434]: can't capture dynamic environment in a fn item\r\n --> test.rs:3:9\r\n  |\r\n3 |         a\r\n  |         ^\r\n  |\r\n  = help: use the `|| { ... }` closure form instead\r\n  ```\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: no error\r\n\r\nThis is invalid, since the name resolution rules state that only closures are able to access their outer environment, not inner functions.\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\n\r\n- What version of Rust GCC were you using, git sha if possible.\r\n\r\ne8d00353017\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/issues/2296/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/issues/2296/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}